// ==================
// CAMPAIGN: STANDARD
// ==================
// stage values
// =========================================================
// delay	V_DATE (year, day, hour)	delay after getting activated
// frame	V_DATE (year, day, hour)	only day and hour are used to randomize the activation
// expire	V_DATE (year, day, hour)	time after which the mission expires
// seq		V_STRING	sequence id to play
// missions	V_STRING	string of missions included in this stage
// number	V_INT		how many missions needs to appear on geoscape until next set is called
// quota	V_INT		how many missions needs to be done until next set is called
// needed	V_STRING	need another stage to be finished?
// nextstage	V_STRING	which is the next stage we should enter?
// endstage	V_STRING
// commands	V_STRING	console command
//
// mission values
// =========================================================
// text		V_TRANSLATION_STRING	"_translated"	(marked with _ to let the parser detect the string as translatable)
// map		V_STRING		africa04	a valid map file without d or n (for day and night map - last char of mapname)
//							this string may contain a + as first char - this means that this is a random assembled map (see *.ump)
//							with . as first char we have a base attack map
// param	V_STRING		commercial	this if for maps with + as first char - sets the map style (see *.ump)
// music	V_STRING		mission		music from base/music *.ogg
// pos		V_POS			"-82 125"	x, y
// aliens	V_INT			5		how many aliens in this mission?
// alienteam	V_STRING		alien		which alienrace?
// alienequip	V_STRING				campaign_alien	which equipment the alien uses in this mission
// civilians	V_INT			6		how many civilians will be in the mission?
// civteam	V_STRING		oriental	which race of civilians
// recruits	V_INT			3		how many recruits/soldiers you are allowed to carry to battle
// $win		V_INT			1200		how much credits you will get on win
// $alien	V_INT			100		how much credits for each killed alien
// $civilian	V_INT			500		how much you will lose for each killed civilian
//
// campaign values
// =========================================================
// name		V_STRING	"_Standard Campaign"		name of campaign
// text		V_STRING	"_txt_standard_campaign"	campaign description
// team		V_STRING	human				which team?
// soldiers	V_INT		12				how many soldiers in this campaign?
// equipment	V_STRING	campaign_player			which equipment to use
// market	V_STRING	campaign_market			which market definition to use
// credits	V_INT		500000				how much credits at start
// map		V_STRING	map_earth			which map to use for geoscape
// visible	V_BOOL		true				is this campaign visible in campaign list
// date		V_DATE		"2000 0 7"			starting date
// firststage	V_STRING	intro				first stage to enter
//
//
//
//
